<div class="helpBody">
<h2>Changing forum template settings</h2>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> To complete these procedures, you must be
assigned a role having the necessary permissions.  To determine your
role, follow the directions in <a href="content.hlp?docId=arbu">Participant roles</a>.  For a basic understanding of roles and
permissions, see <a href="content.hlp?docId=arax">Permissions and roles: Overview</a>.</p>

<p>The template settings in Forums apply by default each time you create
a new forum or topic, although you can override the default settings
for each specific forum or topic as you create or revise them (see
<a href="content.hlp?docId=asci">Creating new forums and topics</a> or <a href="content.hlp?docId=atdk">Revising or deleting a forum or topic</a>).  To change the template settings that will apply
to all future forums and topics:</p>

<ol><li>In your site's <a href="content.hlp?docId=arcc">menubar</a>, click <strong><code>Forums</code></strong>, and then
click <strong><code>Template Settings</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Set each of the following to your desired default setting:

<br /><br />

<ul><li><strong>Forum Posting:</strong> Choose whether topics will be
moderated and whether
participants must post before reading others' contributions.
</li><li><strong>Availability:</strong> Choose
to display the forum immediately, or set specific dates to open and
close it to participants.
</li><li><strong>Mark All Messages in
Conversations Read:</strong> Changing this setting will automatically
mark messages in a given conversation as read when the first message
in the conversation is opened.
</li><li><strong>Permissions:</strong> For more about the permission settings
 you can modify, see <a href="content.hlp?docId=atdt">Controlling access in Forums</a>.
</li></ul>
<br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Save</code></strong> to save your changes.
</li></ol>

</div>
